      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ESCAPING BINDI (4) slotted in just off the lead from the wide draw last start and boxed on to finish second (30.00) at this track in a Grade 5 over 515m. Rates highly and will give a great sight. BLINKED (3) was unwanted in betting when starting from the same box but ran very well, finishing in the minors over 515m at this track in a Grade 5 in 30.19. Should be in this for a long way. LISA ROSE (1) was never in contention last time after being shuffled back early at Bendigo, but prior to that won by half a length at Warragul (22.90) beating Winter Goes in a Grade 5 H NP on June 4. Worth another chance. REEL INFRARED (2) scored last time and can measure up again.",
